law.text: Each member of the board shall serve for a term of three (3) years and until his successor is appointed and qualified. Appointments to fill vacancies shall be for the unexpired term, and shall be made in accordance with the provisions of KRS 312.015 to 312.175.
law.history: Amended 1980 Ky. Acts ch. 188, sec. 185, effective July 15, 1980. -- Created 1962 Ky. Acts ch. 179, sec. 3, effective June 14, 1962.
